cs.CV, cs.AR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY. 

The paper focuses on implementing Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN) on FPGA for domain-specific applications, specifically for image recognition tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses transfer learning, which falls under the category of cs.AR (Augmented Reality and Virtual Reality). The use of efficient convolution blocks and layer fusion techniques can be considered as optimization techniques, which are commonly discussed in the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the deployment of CNN on FPGA can be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
